<subSubSection id="97BB058D595D1184D75542A505E3232F" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9C8D4296F9DC79B20D26DFF5D598917E" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB06F0E17FCD4DE39D6B4564D91F062F" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="D0DDC2A3DB6624F79670519465A2E755" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes barbatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis id="A9A629EA4B5ED51EC280333D3ACA9AAD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Sphecodes barbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="40E0A04B97C3BD34B9CAC51B4688F484" genus="S." lsidName="S. majalis" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="42C4F54D2778644D7C62178844826112" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species are easily separable in the female, but males are difficult. The female 
<taxonomicName id="E90E636E3FBF6890B58F76BA58CB9C12" genus="S." lsidName="S. barbatus" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis id="2E8FC710C7ECE72EFA3237A9D917377F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. barbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A7E3C1F996F84877742AC33ADDF5754D" genus="S." lsidName="S. majalis" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="BC8C1E4C5119B253CEAD98071BE4D461" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by denser, distinctly plumose pubescence on paraocular areas and clypeus (
<figureCitation id="CEAE83AC840665410A1C70220BFA3BF6" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Head, females, frontal view. 2 Sphecodes majalis Perez 3 S. scabricollis Wesmael 4 S. barbatus Bluethgen 5 S. atlanticus Warncke 6 S. rubripes Spinola 7 S. albilabris (Fabricius). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.872.35361.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/327081" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) (sparser, weakly plumose or simple pubescence in 
<taxonomicName id="861ED28C5F7534269A10762937B9A976" genus="S." lsidName="S. majalis" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="188B593A33B9A04B6BEB4CAADC59B106" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="EE452994C0ABED440A857F8BECDF259B" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Head, females, frontal view. 2 Sphecodes majalis Perez 3 S. scabricollis Wesmael 4 S. barbatus Bluethgen 5 S. atlanticus Warncke 6 S. rubripes Spinola 7 S. albilabris (Fabricius). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.872.35361.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/327081" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and by a distinctly (
<figureCitation id="2845671BF1F2C69FAB3EDE1EE6E051B9" captionStart="Figures 16–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 19. T 1 (16, 17), metasoma (18, 19), females, dorsal view. 16 Sphecodes majalis Perez 17 S. barbatus Bluethgen 18 S. scabricollis Wesmael 19 S. atlanticus Warncke. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.872.35361.figures16-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/327084" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) punctate T1 (sparse and tiny punctures in 
<taxonomicName id="31044C8559CE170244F0C9A94CBD04E9" genus="S." lsidName="S. majalis" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="7AAA1A511114DEE8AE3C0DBFC9839F90" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="9BBCD454759CABDFEB435CA6B995C0D8" captionStart="Figures 16–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 19. T 1 (16, 17), metasoma (18, 19), females, dorsal view. 16 Sphecodes majalis Perez 17 S. barbatus Bluethgen 18 S. scabricollis Wesmael 19 S. atlanticus Warncke. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.872.35361.figures16-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/327084" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
